abstract: Nate Chinen reviews performance by trumpeter Wynton Marsalis as part of his jazz program Spaces, also featuring dancers Lil Buck and Jared Grimes, at Rose Theater.
lead_paragraph: In this premiere, the Jazz at Lincoln Center Orchestra moved from buzzing kazoos for bees to clucking reeds to an elephantine harrumph by clarinets and trombones.

headline.main: Review: Wynton Marsalis’s ‘Spaces,’ a Kinetic Series of Zoological Portraits
